models.classes

Class Board

  • java.lang.Object
    • models.classes.Board

  • public class Board
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents the grid on which the Player places his Dominos. It contains all the methods related to the management of all Dominos. It also monitors, depending on the GameMode, that the size of the game remains in accordance with the rules.

    • Method Detail

      • getPossibilities

        public java.util.List<java.util.List<Position>> getPossibilities(Domino domino)
        Returns all possibles Position for a Domino. This method first recovers all the Position available for the Domino passed as parameter, depending on its orientation. Then, it checks that these Position will not make the Board exceed its regulatory size.
        Parameters:
        domino - Domino for which we want to have the possible positions.
        Returns:
        List] of {@link Position} {@link List} containing all possible {@link Position}s for the {@link Domino} passed as parameter. All {@link List] of {@link Position}s contains only two of the latter. Indeed, as each {@link Domino} is composed of two {@link LandPortion}, a {@link Position} must be provided for each of them.

      • isPossibleToPlaceDomino

        public boolean isPossibleToPlaceDomino(Position position1,
                                       Position position2,
                                       Domino domino)
        Check if it's possible to place the Domino passed as parameter to the position1 and position2 according to its Rotation.
        Parameters:
        position1 - Position of one of the two LandPortion of the Domino.
        position2 - Position of one of the two LandPortion of the Domino.
        domino - Domino whose possibility of being place at position1 and position2 is checked.
        Returns:
        true if the Domino can be placed to the position1 and position2. false otherwise.

      • calculateGridMaxSize

        public void calculateGridMaxSize()
        Calculates the maxGridSize possible while respecting all rules. This updates the grid attribute. It calculates the Positions of the extremes of the Board. This function allows you to know if you can place a Domino for example in a Position without exceeding the size of the regulatory Board.

      • addDomino

        public void addDomino(Domino domino)
               throws InvalidDominoPosition
        Adds a Domino to the list of Dominos selected by the Board's Player owner. If the Domino has a Position, this checks if it can be added on the Board by respecting the connection rules. This impacts the view of the Board too.
        Parameters:
        domino - Domino which the Player wants to add.
        Throws:
        InvalidDominoPosition - If the Domino cant be added to the Board's Player according to it's Position.

      • removeDomino

        public void removeDomino(Domino domino)
        Removes a Domino to the list of Dominos selected by the Board's Player owner. Take care, this doesn't impact the view of the Board. If you want to, see DominoesListView.removeDominoView(Domino).
        Parameters:
        domino - Domino which the Player wants to remove.

      • getGrid

        public java.util.List<Position> getGrid()
        Gets the grid of the Board. This is a list of Positions on which Dominos are allowed to be placed on it. Outside this list, the Domino cannot be placed without violating the regulatory size.
